reviews_data.review_text:
I come to this location almost every Saturday and consider it one of my favorite coffee shops in CLT. Today I placed a mobile order for 5 drinks. When I arrived, the last drink was just being finished, so I began checking the cups to see which was which, but none were labeled. I asked one of the baristas for clarification, and was taken aback when she responded, “We’re too busy right now, I can’t help you with that.” I could tell by the look on her face she wasn’t having the best day.

Not only did this come across as dismissive, but it is certainly part of the job to label drinks or at least inform the customer which is which as they’ve done before. I work in hospitality myself as a bartender/server, I  was also a barista and I would never say that to someone. I appreciate the other barista that apologized and told me that shouldn’t have happened so I let it go and went about my day.

I rarely leave reviews, but I felt the need to share this experience in hopes it can be taken as constructive feedback.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Ashley,

Thank you for sharing your experience with us. We’re grateful that you visit us regularly and consider our shop one of your favorites in Charlotte. I’m very sorry to hear about your recent order and the way your request for clarification was handled. You are right—labeling drinks or ensuring guests know which is which is an important part of our service, and your interaction should have been more attentive.

We’ll be addressing this with our team so that it doesn’t happen again, especially during our busier times. I also appreciate you acknowledging the other barista who stepped in—that’s the standard of service we want every guest to experience.

Thank you again for taking the time to leave thoughtful feedback. We hope to provide you with the consistently positive service you’ve come to expect on your next visit.

Sincerely,

Anthony, Owner

reviews_data.review_text:
I come to this location almost every Saturday and consider it one of my favorite coffee shops in CLT. Today I placed a mobile order for 5 drinks. When I arrived, the last drink was just being finished, so I began checking the cups to see which was which, but none were labeled. I asked one of the baristas for clarification, and was taken aback when she responded, “We’re too busy right now, I can’t help you with that.” I could tell by the look on her face she wasn’t having the best day.

Not only did this come across as dismissive, but it is certainly part of the job to label drinks or at least inform the customer which is which as they’ve done before. I work in hospitality myself as a bartender/server, I  was also a barista and I would never say that to someone. I appreciate the other barista that apologized and told me that shouldn’t have happened so I let it go and went about my day.

I rarely leave reviews, but I felt the need to share this experience in hopes it can be taken as constructive feedback.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Ashley,

Thank you for sharing your experience with us. We’re grateful that you visit us regularly and consider our shop one of your favorites in Charlotte. I’m very sorry to hear about your recent order and the way your request for clarification was handled. You are right—labeling drinks or ensuring guests know which is which is an important part of our service, and your interaction should have been more attentive.

We’ll be addressing this with our team so that it doesn’t happen again, especially during our busier times. I also appreciate you acknowledging the other barista who stepped in—that’s the standard of service we want every guest to experience.

Thank you again for taking the time to leave thoughtful feedback. We hope to provide you with the consistently positive service you’ve come to expect on your next visit.

Sincerely,

Anthony, Owner
